load ../workflow-authority-attenuation.maude

--- ============================ COVERAGE ======================================

--- Coverage: without an explicit start grant, the child receives the automatic
--- cap: declared(child) intersect effective(parent).
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-WORKFLOW-AUTHORITY-ATTENUATION :
  parentEffective(read ; write) childDeclared(read ; model) noStartGrant childAuth(mt)
  =>! parentEffective(read ; write) childDeclared(mt) noStartGrant childAuth(read) .

--- Coverage: an explicit start grant that is inside the automatic cap is honored.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-WORKFLOW-AUTHORITY-ATTENUATION :
  parentEffective(read ; write ; exec) childDeclared(read ; write) startGrant(read) childAuth(mt)
  =>! parentEffective(read ; write ; exec) childDeclared(read ; write) startGrant(mt) childAuth(read) .

--- Coverage: a mixed explicit grant keeps the in-cap authority and drops the
--- out-of-cap request.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-WORKFLOW-AUTHORITY-ATTENUATION :
  parentEffective(read ; write) childDeclared(read ; exec) startGrant(read ; exec) childAuth(mt)
  =>! parentEffective(read ; write) childDeclared(read ; exec) startGrant(mt) childAuth(read) .

--- ============================ BITE ==========================================

--- Bite: the automatic cap never grants an authority the parent lacks.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-WORKFLOW-AUTHORITY-ATTENUATION :
  parentEffective(read) childDeclared(read ; write) noStartGrant childAuth(mt)
  =>* childAuth(write ; E:CapSet) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: an explicit start grant cannot widen beyond the parent effective
--- authority, even if the child declares the requested authority.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-WORKFLOW-AUTHORITY-ATTENUATION :
  parentEffective(read) childDeclared(read ; write) startGrant(write) childAuth(mt)
  =>* childAuth(write ; E:CapSet) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: an explicit start grant cannot widen beyond the child declaration, even
--- if the parent has the requested authority.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-WORKFLOW-AUTHORITY-ATTENUATION :
  parentEffective(read ; exec) childDeclared(read) startGrant(exec) childAuth(mt)
  =>* childAuth(exec ; E:CapSet) RESIDUAL:Cfg .
